<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="513" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,289,530]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,325,350]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Remarks.</emphasis>
The large proportion of black on the head and mesothorax along with the transverse black fascia on the anterior pronotal collar are unique to the species within the genus. The species has been associated with the Chaco floristic province in 
<collectingCountry box="[456,567,397,422]" name="Argentina" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(Sanborn, 
<emphasis box="[691,739,397,422]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[754,812,398,422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn" box="[836,1096,397,422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S. (2014) The cicadas of Argentina with new records, a new genus and fifteen new species (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 3883 (1), 1 - 94. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3883.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Sanborn &amp; Heath 
<number box="[1038,1096,398,422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) being collected over much of the north-central region of the country (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn" box="[594,859,433,458]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S. (2014) The cicadas of Argentina with new records, a new genus and fifteen new species (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 3883 (1), 1 - 94. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3883.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Sanborn &amp; Heath 
<number box="[798,859,433,457]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
